Title: Vista
Author: Pacze Moj
Publisher: Pirate Cove Publishing


From the back cover:

&quot;Pacze Moj&amp;#039;s debut story explores the blurred line between utopia and dystopia -- a division that seemingly becomes harder and harder to distinguish as we develop technologies that enable us to mask reality, and live in a world where what we see is increasingly not what is. Although ostensibly light science fiction, &amp;#039;Vista&amp;#039; also containes traces of romance and more than a hint of allegory. Indeed, by the time the last word disappears, you may wonder if the story&amp;#039;s not as much about operating systems as it is about oxygen and memory and lost love.&quot;


About the publisher:

Pirate Cove Publishing (PCP) is an experiment in distributing short-to-medium length works of fiction through The Pirate Bay and other p2p networks.

Since this is the first PCP release, please consider it something of a dress rehearsal: the spirit is there, but the bones are still bare. In the future, I&amp;#039;d like to create a nicer layout and include more content -- including little extras along the lines of what you&amp;#039;d get in those old Infocom text adventure games.

